HEADWORD: Mortpay
<hw>Mort"pay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>mort</ets>
dead + E. <ets>pay</ets>.]</ety> <def>Dead pay; the crime of taking pay
for the service of dead soldiers, or for services not actually rendered
by soldiers.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

